records.addlTxt:
10:33 a.m  Defendant present in court with Atty Erik Johnson.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  State filed an information with the court.  Attorney Johnson and defendant acknowledge receipt of the information and waives any reading.  Atty Johnson enters a plea of No Contest  to count 1 on behalf of the defendant and the balance of the counts will be dismissed.  Court recites agreement, defendant will plea to count 1 and counts 2 & 3 will be dismissed.  State concurs.  Atty Johnson concurs.  Defendant concurs.

Court goes over plea questionnaire with the defendant.  Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights.  Court goes over the elements of each offense.  Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty.  Court instructs defendant regarding deportation.  (If felony) Court instructs regarding felony prohibitions.

Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty on count 1 and orders counts 2 & 3 be dismissed.  Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today.  Sentencing statement by DA.  Sentencing statement by Atty Johnson.  Statement by the defendant.

Court sentences the defendant to:

-SWD, and places the defendant on probation for 2 years.

CONDITIONS:

-Court costs.
-Defendant is to submit a DNA Sample.

Court adjourned at 10:44 a.m.

1:34 p.m.  Defendant present in court with Atty Erik Johnson.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Statement by Atty Johnson - moving towards resolution and defendant will waive his right to a preliminary hearing.  Defendant concurs.  

Court instructs the defendant regarding his right to a preliminary examination.  Defendant waives his right to a preliminary examination.  Court accepts the waiver of the prelim and binds the defendant over for trial.  DA files information today.  Court sets for Arraignment on April 26, 2016 at 10:30 a.m.

Court adjourned at 1:38 p.m.

11:11 A.M.  Defendant present in court with Atty Erik Johnson.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Atty Johnson confirms receipt of the criminal complaint and waives reading.  Court instructs the defendant of the maximum penalty on each count and as repeater.  Court finds probable cause.  ADA makes bond recommendation.  Court sets bond at $500.00 signature bond.  Court instructs defendant regarding his/her right to a preliminary hearing.  Defendant waives the time limits.  Court will set for Status Hearing on March 29, 2016 at 1:30 p.m..

Court adjourned at 11:13 a.m.
